@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Export to Excel";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>@ViewData["Title"]</h2>

    <p>This view demonstrates the export of a list of products to Excel.</p>

    <p>To export the list to Excel, follow these steps:</p>

    <ol>
        <li>Click on the "Export to Excel" button.</li>
        <li>Choose the location where you want to save the Excel file.</li>
        <li>Open the saved Excel file to view the exported data.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>The exported Excel file will contain information about the products, including their names, prices, and other details.</p>

    <p>Thank you for using our export feature!</p>

    <!-- You can add more content or formatting as needed. -->

    <form method="post" action="/Product/ExportToExcel">
        <button type="submit">Export to Excel</button>
    </form>
</body>
</html>
